<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are the 126 counties dropped and 28
counties added this year by the <MONEY>$124.9 million</MONEY> <ORGANIZATION>Emergency Food and
Shelter National Board Program</ORGANIZATION>.
   Funding for counties and grant sizes are reconsidered each year
based on a formula that considers local poverty, unemployment and
the size of the overall labor force. The program was designed ``to
supplement and extend'' efforts on behalf of the homeless, and the
government does not guarantee funding to individual counties beyond
one year.
   DROPPED:
   <LOCATION>Alaska</LOCATION> _ <LOCATION>Anchorage Borough
   Arkansas</LOCATION> _ <PERSON>Clark</PERSON>, <LOCATION>Saline
   Colorado</LOCATION> _ <LOCATION>Fremont</LOCATION>, <PERSON>Montezuma
