co-chairman, <ORGANIZATION>National Conference of Christians</ORGANIZATION> and Jews, <ORGANIZATION>Southern California 
Region</ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON>Calhoun</PERSON>, director of audit for <ORGANIZATION>Ernst &amp; Young</ORGANIZATION> and former managing 
partner of <ORGANIZATION>Arthur Young &amp; Co.</ORGANIZATION>, succeeds <PERSON>Edward Sanders</PERSON>, who remains a 
co-chairman. Sanders is an attorney with <PERSON>Sanders</PERSON>, <PERSON>Jacobson</PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION>Goldman &amp; Mosk</ORGANIZATION>. 
