Facing the <LOCATION>Detroit</LOCATION> {of today}, I was frightened -- not for my safety, but for the future of these children . . . . 
The kids are colossally, terribly alone." 

   Says a mother at <ORGANIZATION>Henry Horner Homes</ORGANIZATION>: "Bringing up a child where I do, you can lose them." 
Indeed, we've already lost entire communities. 

